text: Kate Gynther (born 5 July 1982 in Brisbane) is a water polo player from Australia. She won a bronze medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics when she played for the team from Australia. She played water polo at the 2004 Summer Olympics; her team finished fourth. == References == ==Other websites== Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:2008 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Australia Category:Sportspeople from Brisbane Category:Australian water polo players
